**Bug 1 — Invalidation check is too aggressive**:[^2_10]
The 2% invalidation check runs inside the same loop that looks for the break candle. This means if any candle during the wait period drops 2% below the break level, the entire setup is killed — even if the break hasn't been attempted yet. This is too strict and will kill valid setups on normal volatility.

**Fix:** Move the invalidation check to only apply after the break candle is found, not during the search.

